	<entry>
		<title>Freeform drawing</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://www.highcharts.com/docs/advanced-chart-features/freeform-drawing"/>
		<published>2013-08-22T09:27:43+00:00</published>
		<updated>2013-08-22T09:27:43+00:00</updated>
		<id>http://www.highcharts.com/docs/advanced-chart-features/freeform-drawing</id>
		<author>
			<name>Super User</name>
			<email>torstein@highsoft.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;div class=&quot;feed-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h1&gt;
    Freeform drawing&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
    Internally, Highcharts is equipped with a rendering module that acts as a wrapper for JavaScript access to SVG in modern browsers and VML in IE &amp;lt; 9. It has much in common with drawing tools like Rapha&amp;euml;l or SVG jQuery. This drawing module can be used either to draw shapes or text on the chart, or even as a standalone drawing tool for HTML pages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
    Inside a chart, the chart&amp;#39;s renderer object is available as &lt;em&gt;chart.renderer&lt;/em&gt;. To instanciate a new SVG drawing outside Highcharts, you call new &lt;em&gt;Highcharts.Renderer(parentNode, width, height)&lt;/em&gt;, where parentNode is the div or container element where you want the drawing to be placed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
    The drawing API is documented in detail at &lt;a href=&quot;http://api.highcharts.com#Renderer&quot;&gt;api.highcharts.com#Renderer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://api.highcharts.com#Element&quot;&gt;api.highcharts.com#Element&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;div class=&quot;feed-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h1&gt;
    Freeform drawing&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
    Internally, Highcharts is equipped with a rendering module that acts as a wrapper for JavaScript access to SVG in modern browsers and VML in IE &amp;lt; 9. It has much in common with drawing tools like Rapha&amp;euml;l or SVG jQuery. This drawing module can be used either to draw shapes or text on the chart, or even as a standalone drawing tool for HTML pages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
    Inside a chart, the chart&amp;#39;s renderer object is available as &lt;em&gt;chart.renderer&lt;/em&gt;. To instanciate a new SVG drawing outside Highcharts, you call new &lt;em&gt;Highcharts.Renderer(parentNode, width, height)&lt;/em&gt;, where parentNode is the div or container element where you want the drawing to be placed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
    The drawing API is documented in detail at &lt;a href=&quot;http://api.highcharts.com#Renderer&quot;&gt;api.highcharts.com#Renderer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://api.highcharts.com#Element&quot;&gt;api.highcharts.com#Element&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
